subject: The prefix "xsltu" for element "xsltu.tests" is not bound.
msgSnippet: I am working on creating a unit test for xslt. I am trying to follow the work example in XSLTunit at http://xslunit.org/0/2/. I have created this XSLT unit
messageBody:
I am working on creating a unit test for xslt. I am trying to follow
the work example in XSLTunit at http://xslunit.org/0/2/. I have
created this XSLT unit suite and I am receiving an xsltu.tests is not
bound.
What have I missed? Any help would be appreciated.
Thank you in advance.

-- XSLT unit suite code --

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<xsl:stylesheet version="1.0"
xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/2001/XSLSchema-instance">
<xsl:import href="resultviewer.xsl" />
<xsl:import href="http://xsltunit.org/0/2/xsltunit.xsl" />
<xsl:output method="xml" version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"
indent="yes" />
<xsl:template match="/">
<xsltu:tests>
<xsltu:test id="test-policy number">
<xsl:call-template name="xsltu:assertEqual">
<xsl:with-param name="id" select="'full-value'" />
<xsl:with-param name="nodes1">
<xsl:apply-templates select="document
('HoldingResponse.xml')/TXLife/TXLifeResponse/OLifE/Holding id/Policy
id/PolNumber" />
</xsl:with-param>
<xsl:with-param name="nodes2">
<h1>YSMVRDP006</h1>
</xsl:with-param>
</xsl:call-template>
</xsltu:test>
</xsltu:tests>
</xsl:template>
</xsl:stylesheet>
